        ic - The IRC Command to send.

      • postEvent

        Queues an IrcEvent message object for processing.

      • sendEvent

        public IrcEventAction sendEvent(IrcEvent event)
                         throws Exception
        Synchronously processes an IrcEvent object against plugins This method should generally not be used by plugins if it can be avoided. Prefer postEvent() instead. PLUGIN event messages will cause the plugin to be enabled or disabled within the time of this function call.
        Parameters:
        event - Event to be processed
        Returns:
        The event action indicated by plugin(s). CANCEL_EVENT implies higher post-processing (such as data transmission actions) should be canceled.
        Throws:
        Exception - An error occurred within a plugin event handler.
        See Also:
        postEvent(IrcEvent)

      • findPlugin

        public IrcPlugin findPlugin(String name_search)
        Find a plugin object instance by the plugin name This only searches loaded plugins.
        Parameters:
        name_search - The plugin name to check for.
        Returns:
        The instance of the matching plugin is returned, otherwise 'null' is returned for no match.

      • enablePlugin

        public void enablePlugin(String name)
        Queue a request for a plugin to be enabled When the plugin is enabled, it will receive Events (all plugins are by default enabled) NOTE: this takes effect when the PLUGIN message is "sent" next, not immediately.
        Parameters:
        name - Name of the plugin to enable (corresponds to IrcPlugin.name)

      • disablePlugin

        public void disablePlugin(String name)
        Queue a request for a plugin to be disabled When the plugin is disabled, it will not receive Events (all plugins are by default enabled) NOTE: this takes effect when the PLUGIN message is "sent" next, not immediately.
        Parameters:
        name - Name of the plugin to disable (corresponds to IrcPlugin.name)

      • addPlugin

        public void addPlugin(IrcPlugin plugin)
        Add a plugin object instance to the plugins enabled for the bot. The plugin will receive events dispatched by the Plugin Manager afterwards.
        Parameters:
        plugin - The plugin object to communicate with.

      • loadPlugins

        public int loadPlugins()
                throws URISyntaxException
        Search the plugins directory [relative to the bot jar/class] for plugin JARs and load+enable them
        Returns:
        number of plugins loaded.
        Throws:
        URISyntaxException - An error occurred while constructing the plugin directory path.
